<paper id="1571335534"><title>Applying COGEX to recognize textual entailment</title><year>2005</year><authors><author org="Language Computer Corporation, Richardson, TX" id="2034371461">Daniel Hodges</author><author org="Language Computer Corporation, Richardson, TX" id="2099662501">Christine Clark</author><author org="Language Computer Corporation, Richardson, TX" id="2121542485">Abraham Fowler</author><author org="Language Computer Corporation, Richardson, TX" id="2311416189">Dan Moldovan</author></authors><n_citation>39</n_citation><doc_type>Conference</doc_type><references><reference>1482728761</reference><reference>1498515764</reference><reference>1990812879</reference><reference>2005148043</reference><reference>2013434344</reference><reference>2080278171</reference><reference>2092654472</reference><reference>2103273389</reference><reference>2129967282</reference><reference>2130158090</reference><reference>2158937425</reference><reference>2525127255</reference><reference>2595842645</reference></references><venue id="1180662882" type="C">International Conference on Machine Learning</venue><doi>10.1007/11736790_24</doi><keywords><keyword weight="0.62645">Text graph</keyword><keyword weight="0.72248">Textual entailment</keyword><keyword weight="0.44254">Computer science</keyword><keyword weight="0.52286">Proof theory</keyword><keyword weight="0.5522">Natural language</keyword><keyword weight="0.46986">Natural language processing</keyword><keyword weight="0.0">Artificial intelligence</keyword><keyword weight="0.5535">Abductive reasoning</keyword><keyword weight="0.51353">Parsing</keyword><keyword weight="0.5682">Logic form</keyword><keyword weight="0.51352">Semantics</keyword></keywords><publisher>Springer, Berlin, Heidelberg</publisher><abstract>This paper describes the system that LCC has devised to perform textual entailment recognition for the PASCAL RTE Challenge. Our system transforms each text-hypothesis pair into a two-layered logic form representation that expresses the lexical, syntactic, and semantic attributes of the text and hypothesis. A large set of natural language axioms are constructed for each text-hypothesis pair that help connect concepts in the hypothesis with concepts in the text. Our natural language logic prover is then used to prove entailment through abductive reasoning. The systemu0027s performance in the challenge resulted in an accuracy of 55%.</abstract></paper>